BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU Media School
DTSTART:20260424T173000Z
DTEND:20260424T184500Z
LOCATION:FRANKLIN HALL - Room Number: 312
GEO:39.167025;-86.526406
SUMMARY:'The (In)visibility Paradox:' a talk with Réka Benczes
DESCRIPTION:Focusing on a recent study of featured images from leading Hu
 ngarian online news outlets to draw on visual discourse analysis and conc
 eptual metonymy theory\, the results shed light on what we term the (In)v
 isibility Paradox\; although older women are numerically more visible tha
 n men\, they are more likely to appear in passive\, caregiving\, or econo
 mically vulnerable representations. This is opposed to the way men are de
 picted in roles of autonomy\, resilience\, and competence.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Focusing on a recent study of featured 
 images from leading Hungarian online news outlets to draw on visual disco
 urse analysis and conceptual metonymy theory\, the results shed light on 
 what we term the (In)visibility Paradox\; although older women are numeri
 cally more visible than men\, they are more likely to appear in passive\,
  caregiving\, or economically vulnerable representations. This is opposed
  to the way men are depicted in roles of autonomy\, resilience\, and comp
 etence.</p>
UID:20260424T173000Z-2262214@events.iu.edu
DTSTAMP:20260408T130236Z
URL:https://events.iu.edu/mediaiub/event/2262214-the-invisibility-paradox
 -a-talk-with-rka-benczes
